ce:section.ce:para:
In the conventional autoclave solvothermal method, pure anthracene was first transformed into 9,10-dinitroanthracene in aqueous HNO3 media under reflux conditions, following which denitration via a substitution reaction in alkaline media (under reflux conditions) gave 9,10-dihydroxyanthracene (Fig. 1
                        ). The synthesis of the CQDs was also performed in several other solvents (acetone, methanol, hexane, ethanol, water, dimethyl sulfoxide, ethylene glycol and N-methyl-2-pyrorridone) to investigate the photoluminescence of each of the resulting (albeit unpurified) carbon products (Fig. 2
                        a). Subsequent intramolecular dehydration and condensation led to the polymerization of the carbon precursor molecules and to the production of blue (with hexane), green (with acetone, dimethyl sulfoxide), and yellow (with methanol, ethanol and ethylene glycol) emitting carbonaceous products (Figs. 1 and 2a).
